Note: Advanced Conditional Planning System for AI Agents
Implements contingency planning, uncertainty handling, branching plans,
observation actions, and dynamic plan adaptation under uncertainty
Competitive with PKS, Contingent-FF, and conditional planning systems:End Note

Note: Core conditional planning types
Type ConditionalPlan is Dictionary with:
    plan id as String
    plan name as String
    plan type as String  Note: "fully_conditional", "conformant", "contingent"
    root branch as PlanBranch
    observation actions as List[ObservationAction]
    uncertainty model as UncertaintyModel
    plan quality as Float
    expected cost as Float
    success probability as Float
    contingency depth as Integer

Type PlanBranch is Dictionary with:
    branch id as String
    branch condition as BranchCondition
    branch actions as List[ConditionalAction]
    child branches as List[PlanBranch]
    observation points as List[ObservationPoint]
    branch probability as Float
    branch cost as Float
    branch utility as Float
    execution context as ExecutionContext

Type ConditionalAction is Dictionary with:
    action id as String
    action name as String
    action type as String  Note: "primitive", "observation", "conditional", "nondeterministic"
    base action as Action
    execution conditions as List[Condition]
    failure modes as List[FailureMode]
    success probability as Float
    outcome distribution as OutcomeDistribution
    context requirements as List[String]

Type ObservationAction is Dictionary with:
    observation id as String
    observation name as String
    observation type as String  Note: "sensor", "query", "test", "monitor"
    observable variables as List[String]
    observation cost as Float
    observation duration as Integer
    observation reliability as Float
    possible outcomes as List[ObservationOutcome]

Type BranchCondition is Dictionary with:
    condition id as String
    condition type as String  Note: "state_based", "observation_based", "probabilistic", "temporal"
    logical expression as LogicalExpression
    probability threshold as Float
    confidence level as Float
    evaluation context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type UncertaintyModel is Dictionary with:
    model id as String
    model type as String  Note: "probabilistic", "possibilistic", "interval", "fuzzy"
    uncertain variables as List[UncertainVariable]
    probabilistic effects as List[ProbabilisticEffect]
    observation model as ObservationModel
    transition model as TransitionModel

Type UncertainVariable is Dictionary with:
    variable id as String
    variable name as String
    variable type as String
    value domain as List[Any]
    probability distribution as Distribution
    observability as String  Note: "fully_observable", "partially_observable", "unobservable"
    uncertainty source as String

Type ObservationOutcome is Dictionary with:
    outcome id as String
    outcome value as Any
    outcome probability as Float
    outcome reliability as Float
    information gain as Float
    observation cost as Float

Type ConditionalPlanningProblem is Dictionary with:
    problem id as String
    problem name as String
    initial belief state as BeliefState
    goal conditions as List[Condition]
    available actions as List[ConditionalAction]
    observation actions as List[ObservationAction]
    uncertainty model as UncertaintyModel
    planning horizon as Integer
    success criteria as List[Criterion]

Note: Conditional Planning Engine
Process called "create_conditional_planner" that takes config as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let planner be create_conditional_planner_structure
    Set planner with key "planner_id" to generate_conditional_planner_id
    Set planner with key "planning_algorithm" to config with key "algorithm" or "contingent_planning"
    Set planner with key "uncertainty_reasoning" to config with key "uncertainty" or "probabilistic"
    Set planner with key "observation_strategy" to config with key "observation" or "information_gain"
    Set planner with key "branching_factor_limit" to config with key "max_branches" or 10
    Set planner with key "planning_depth_limit" to config with key "max_depth" or 15
    Set planner with key "success_threshold" to config with key "success_threshold" or 0.8
    Set planner with key "cost_bound" to config with key "max_cost" or 1000.0
    
    Return planner

Process called "plan_with_conditions" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ConditionalPlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let start_time be current_timestamp
    Let planning_algorithm be planner with key "planning_algorithm"
    
    Let planning_result be empty dictionary
    
    If planning_algorithm is equal to "contingent_planning":
        Set planning_result to contingent_planning_algorithm with planner and problem
    
    If planning_algorithm is equal to "conformant_planning":
        Set planning_result to conformant_planning_algorithm with planner and problem
    
    If planning_algorithm is equal to "fully_conditional":
        Set planning_result to fully_conditional_planning with planner and problem
    
    If planning_algorithm is equal to "and_or_search":
        Set planning_result to and_or_search_planning with planner and problem
    
    Let end_time be current_timestamp
    Set planning_result with key "planning_time" to end_time minus start_time
    
    Return planning_result

Process called "contingent_planning_algorithm" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ConditionalPlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "success" to false
    
    Let initial_belief_state be problem with field initial_belief_state
    Let goal_conditions be problem with field goal_conditions
    Let available_actions be problem with field available_actions
    Let observation_actions be problem with field observation_actions
    
    Note: Initialize contingent planning search
    Let search_queue be create_priority_queue
    Let explored_states be create_set
    Let best_plan be null
    Let best_cost be positive_infinity
    
    Note: Create initial search node
    Let initial_node be create_contingent_search_node with initial_belief_state and empty list and 0.0 and null
    Add initial_node to search_queue with priority 0.0
    
    Let max_iterations be 10000
    Let iterations be 0
    
    Note: Contingent planning main search loop
    While search_queue is not empty and iterations is less than max_iterations:
        Set iterations to iterations plus 1
        Let current_node be pop_minimum from search_queue
        Let current_belief_state be current_node with key "belief_state"
        Let current_plan_branch be current_node with key "plan_branch"
        Let current_cost be current_node with key "cost"
        
        Note: Check if goal is achieved in all possible states
        Let goal_check be check_goal_achievement_in_belief_state with current_belief_state and goal_conditions
        
        If goal_check with key "achieved" is equal to true:
            If current_cost is less than best_cost:
                Set best_cost to current_cost
                Set best_plan to current_plan_branch
            Continue to next iteration
        
        Note: Generate state signature for duplicate detection
        Let state_signature be generate_belief_state_signature with current_belief_state
        If explored_states contains state_signature:
            Continue to next iteration
        Add state_signature to explored_states
        
        Note: Expand node with possible actions and observations
        Let expansions be expand_contingent_node with current_node and available_actions and observation_actions and planner
        
        For each expansion in expansions:
            Let expansion_cost be current_cost plus expansion with key "cost"
            
            Note: Prune if cost exceeds bound
            If expansion_cost is greater than planner with key "cost_bound":
                Continue to next iteration
            
            Let new_node be create_contingent_search_node with expansion with key "belief_state" and expansion with key "plan_branch" and expansion_cost and current_node
            
            Note: Calculate heuristic priority
            Let heuristic_value be calculate_contingent_heuristic with expansion with key "belief_state" and goal_conditions and planner
            Let priority be expansion_cost plus heuristic_value
            
            Add new_node to search_queue with priority priority
    
    Note: Create final conditional plan
    If best_plan is not equal to null:
        Let conditional_plan be create_conditional_plan_from_branch with best_plan and problem
        Set conditional_plan with field expected_cost to best_cost
        
        Set result with key "success" to true
        Set result with key "plan" to conditional_plan
        Set result with key "search_statistics" to dictionary with keys "iterations", "explored_states", "final_cost":
            "iterations" maps to iterations
            "explored_states" maps to size of explored_states
            "final_cost" maps to best_cost
    Otherwise:
        Set result with key "success" to false
        Set result with key "error" to "No solution found within cost and iteration limits"
    
    Return result

Process called "expand_contingent_node" that takes node as Dictionary and available_actions as List[ConditionalAction] and observation_actions as List[ObservationAction] and planner as Dictionary returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let expansions be empty list
    Let current_belief_state be node with key "belief_state"
    Let current_plan_branch be node with key "plan_branch"
    
    Note: Expand with action applications
    For each action in available_actions:
        Let applicability_check be check_action_applicability_in_belief_state with action and current_belief_state
        
        If applicability_check with key "applicable" is equal to true:
            Let action_outcomes be simulate_action_in_belief_state with action and current_belief_state
            
            For each outcome in action_outcomes:
                Let new_belief_state be outcome with key "resulting_belief_state"
                Let action_cost be outcome with key "cost"
                Let outcome_probability be outcome with key "probability"
                
                Note: Create new plan branch with this action
                Let new_plan_branch be extend_plan_branch with current_plan_branch and action and outcome
                
                Let expansion be dictionary with keys "belief_state", "plan_branch", "cost", "probability", "type":
                    "belief_state" maps to new_belief_state
                    "plan_branch" maps to new_plan_branch
                    "cost" maps to action_cost
                    "probability" maps to outcome_probability
                    "type" maps to "action"
                
                Add expansion to expansions
    
    Note: Expand with observation actions
    For each observation in observation_actions:
        Let observation_utility be calculate_observation_utility with observation and current_belief_state
        
        If observation_utility is greater than 0.0:
            Let observation_outcomes be simulate_observation_in_belief_state with observation and current_belief_state
            
            Note: Create branching structure for observation outcomes
            Let observation_branches be empty list
            
            For each obs_outcome in observation_outcomes:
                Let updated_belief_state be obs_outcome with key "updated_belief_state"
                Let observation_cost be obs_outcome with key "cost"
                Let outcome_probability be obs_outcome with key "probability"
                
                Let obs_branch be create_observation_branch with observation and obs_outcome and current_plan_branch
                Add obs_branch to observation_branches
            
            Note: Create expansion representing the observation action
            Let observation_expansion be dictionary with keys "belief_state", "plan_branch", "cost", "probability", "type", "branches":
                "belief_state" maps to current_belief_state  Note: Belief state before observation
                "plan_branch" maps to current_plan_branch
                "cost" maps to observation with field observation_cost
                "probability" maps to 1.0
                "type" maps to "observation"
                "branches" maps to observation_branches
            
            Add observation_expansion to expansions
    
    Return expansions

Process called "simulate_action_in_belief_state" that takes action as ConditionalAction and belief_state as BeliefState returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let outcomes be empty list
    Let possible_states be belief_state with field possible_states
    Let state_probabilities be belief_state with field state_probabilities
    
    Note: Group states by action outcome
    Let outcome_groups be empty dictionary
    
    For state_index from 0 to length of possible_states minus 1:
        Let state be possible_states with index state_index
        Let state_probability be state_probabilities with index state_index
        
        Note: Simulate action in this specific state
        Let action_result be simulate_action_in_state with action and state
        
        If action_result with key "success" is equal to true:
            Let resulting_state be action_result with key "resulting_state"
            Let outcome_signature be generate_state_signature with resulting_state
            
            If outcome_groups contains key outcome_signature:
                Let existing_group be outcome_groups with key outcome_signature
                Set existing_group with key "total_probability" to existing_group with key "total_probability" plus state_probability
                Add state to existing_group with key "source_states"
            Otherwise:
                Let new_group be dictionary with keys "resulting_state", "total_probability", "source_states", "cost":
                    "resulting_state" maps to resulting_state
                    "total_probability" maps to state_probability
                    "source_states" maps to list containing state
                    "cost" maps to action with field base_action with field execution_cost
                
                Set outcome_groups with key outcome_signature to new_group
    
    Note: Convert outcome groups to outcome list
    For each outcome_signature in keys of outcome_groups:
        Let group be outcome_groups with key outcome_signature
        
        Note: Create new belief state for this outcome
        Let new_belief_state be create_belief_state_structure
        Set new_belief_state with field belief_state_id to generate_belief_state_id
        Set new_belief_state with field possible_states to list containing group with key "resulting_state"
        Set new_belief_state with field state_probabilities to list containing group with key "total_probability"
        
        Let outcome be dictionary with keys "resulting_belief_state", "cost", "probability":
            "resulting_belief_state" maps to new_belief_state
            "cost" maps to group with key "cost"
            "probability" maps to group with key "total_probability"
        
        Add outcome to outcomes
    
    Return outcomes

Process called "simulate_observation_in_belief_state" that takes observation as ObservationAction and belief_state as BeliefState returns List[Dictionary]:
    Let observation_outcomes be empty list
    Let possible_states be belief_state with field possible_states
    Let state_probabilities be belief_state with field state_probabilities
    Let observable_variables be observation with field observable_variables
    
    Note: Group states by observation outcome
    Let outcome_groups be empty dictionary
    
    For state_index from 0 to length of possible_states minus 1:
        Let state be possible_states with index state_index
        Let state_probability be state_probabilities with index state_index
        
        Note: Determine what would be observed in this state
        Let observed_values be extract_observable_values with state and observable_variables
        Let observation_signature be create_observation_signature with observed_values
        
        If outcome_groups contains key observation_signature:
            Let existing_group be outcome_groups with key observation_signature
            Set existing_group with key "total_probability" to existing_group with key "total_probability" plus state_probability
            Add state to existing_group with key "states"
        Otherwise:
            Let new_group be dictionary with keys "observed_values", "total_probability", "states":
                "observed_values" maps to observed_values
                "total_probability" maps to state_probability
                "states" maps to list containing state
            
            Set outcome_groups with key observation_signature to new_group
    
    Note: Create observation outcomes
    For each observation_signature in keys of outcome_groups:
        Let group be outcome_groups with key observation_signature
        
        Note: Create updated belief state after observation
        Let updated_belief_state be create_belief_state_structure
        Set updated_belief_state with field belief_state_id to generate_belief_state_id
        Set updated_belief_state with field possible_states to group with key "states"
        
        Note: Renormalize probabilities within this observation outcome
        Let states_in_outcome be group with key "states"
        Let renormalized_probabilities be empty list
        Let normalization_factor be group with key "total_probability"
        
        For each state in states_in_outcome:
            Let original_index be find_state_index with possible_states and state
            Let original_probability be state_probabilities with index original_index
            Let renormalized_probability be original_probability divided by normalization_factor
            Add renormalized_probability to renormalized_probabilities
        
        Set updated_belief_state with field state_probabilities to renormalized_probabilities
        
        Let observation_outcome be dictionary with keys "observed_values", "updated_belief_state", "cost", "probability":
            "observed_values" maps to group with key "observed_values"
            "updated_belief_state" maps to updated_belief_state
            "cost" maps to observation with field observation_cost
            "probability" maps to group with key "total_probability"
        
        Add observation_outcome to observation_outcomes
    
    Return observation_outcomes

Note: Conformant Planning (No Observations)
Process called "conformant_planning_algorithm" that takes planner as Dictionary and problem as ConditionalPlanningProblem returns Dictionary:
    Let result be empty dictionary
    Set result with key "success" to false
    
    Let initial_belief_state be problem with field initial_belief_state
    Let goal_conditions be problem with field goal_conditions
    Let available_actions be problem with field available_actions
    
    Note: Conformant planning uses belief state search without observations
    Let search_queue be create_queue
    Let explored_belief_states be create_set
    
    Let initial_search_state be dictionary with keys "belief_state", "action_sequence", "cost":
        "belief_state" maps to initial_belief_state
        "action_sequence" maps to empty list
        "cost" maps to 0.0
    
    Add initial_search_state to search_queue
    
    Let max_iterations be 5000
    Let iterations be 0
    
    Note: Conformant planning search loop
    While search_queue is not empty and iterations is less than max_iterations:
        Set iterations to iterations plus 1
        Let current_state be remove_first from search_queue
        Let current_belief_state be current_state with key "belief_state"
        Let current_sequence be current_state with key "action_sequence"
        Let current_cost be current_state with key "cost"
        
        Note: Check if goal is achieved in all possible states
        Let goal_achieved be check_universal_goal_achievement with current_belief_state and goal_conditions
        
        If goal_achieved is equal to true:
            Let conformant_plan be create_conformant_plan_from_sequence with current_sequence and problem
            Set conformant_plan with field expected_cost to current_cost
            
            Set result with key "success" to true
            Set result with key "plan" to conformant_plan
            Set result with key "search_statistics" to dictionary with keys "iterations", "final_cost":
                "iterations" maps to iterations
                "final_cost" maps to current_cost
            Return result
        
        Note: Generate belief state signature for duplicate detection
        Let belief_signature be generate_belief_state_signature with current_belief_state
        If explored_belief_states contains belief_signature:
            Continue to next iteration
        Add belief_signature to explored_belief_states
        
        Note: Expand with applicable actions
        For each action in available_actions:
            Let action_applicable be check_universal_action_applicability with action and current_belief_state
            
            If action_applicable is equal to true:
                Let resulting_belief_state be apply_action_to_belief_state with action and current_belief_state
                Let action_cost be action with field base_action with field execution_cost
                
                Let new_search_state be dictionary with keys "belief_state", "action_sequence", "cost":
                    "belief_state" maps to resulting_belief_state
                    "action_sequence" maps to append action to current_sequence
                    "cost" maps to current_cost plus action_cost
                
                Add new_search_state to search_queue
    
    Set result with key "success" to false
    Set result with key "error" to "No conformant plan found within iteration limit"
    
    Return result

Process called "check_universal_goal_achievement" that takes belief_state as BeliefState and goal_conditions as List[Condition] returns Boolean:
    Let possible_states be belief_state with field possible_states
    
    Note: Goal must be achieved in ALL possible states
    For each state in possible_states:
        Let state_satisfies_goals be true
        
        For each goal_condition in goal_conditions:
            Let condition_satisfied be evaluate_condition_in_state with goal_condition and state
            If condition_satisfied is equal to false:
                Set state_satisfies_goals to false
                Break from loop
        
        If state_satisfies_goals is equal to false:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "check_universal_action_applicability" that takes action as ConditionalAction and belief_state as BeliefState returns Boolean:
    Let possible_states be belief_state with field possible_states
    Let action_preconditions be action with field base_action with field preconditions
    
    Note: Action must be applicable in ALL possible states
    For each state in possible_states:
        Let action_applicable_in_state be true
        
        For each precondition in action_preconditions:
            Let precondition_satisfied be evaluate_condition_in_state with precondition and state
            If precondition_satisfied is equal to false:
                Set action_applicable_in_state to false
                Break from loop
        
        If action_applicable_in_state is equal to false:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Note: Plan Execution with Contingencies
Process called "execute_conditional_plan" that takes conditional_plan as ConditionalPlan and execution_config as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let execution_result be empty dictionary
    Set execution_result with key "execution_id" to generate_execution_id
    Set execution_result with key "conditional_plan" to conditional_plan
    Set execution_result with key "start_time" to current_timestamp
    
    Let current_branch be conditional_plan with field root_branch
    Let current_belief_state be get_initial_belief_state_from_execution_config with execution_config
    Let execution_trace be empty list
    
    Note: Execute conditional plan by following branches
    While current_branch is not equal to null:
        Let branch_actions be current_branch with field branch_actions
        
        Note: Execute actions in current branch
        For each action in branch_actions:
            Let action_start_time be current_timestamp
            
            Note: Check if action is executable in current context
            Let action_executable be check_action_executability with action and current_belief_state
            
            If action_executable is equal to false:
                Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "action_not_executable"
                Set execution_result with key "failed_action" to action
                Break from loop
            
            Note: Execute action based on its type
            Let action_result be empty dictionary
            
            If action with field action_type is equal to "observation":
                Set action_result to execute_observation_action with action and current_belief_state
            Otherwise:
                Set action_result to execute_primitive_action with action and current_belief_state
            
            Let action_end_time be current_timestamp
            
            Note: Record execution trace
            Let trace_entry be dictionary with keys "action", "start_time", "end_time", "result", "belief_state_before":
                "action" maps to action
                "start_time" maps to action_start_time
                "end_time" maps to action_end_time
                "result" maps to action_result
                "belief_state_before" maps to copy of current_belief_state
            
            Add trace_entry to execution_trace
            
            Note: Update belief state based on action result
            If action_result with key "success" is equal to true:
                Set current_belief_state to action_result with key "updated_belief_state"
            Otherwise:
                Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "action_execution_failed"
                Set execution_result with key "failed_action" to action
                Set execution_result with key "failure_reason" to action_result with key "error"
                Break from loop
        
        Note: Determine next branch based on current state and observations
        Let next_branch be select_next_branch with current_branch and current_belief_state
        Set current_branch to next_branch
        
        Note: Check if we've reached a goal state
        If current_branch is equal to null:
            Let goal_check be check_goal_achievement_in_current_context with current_belief_state and conditional_plan
            If goal_check with key "achieved" is equal to true:
                Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "goal_achieved"
            Otherwise:
                Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "plan_exhausted"
    
    Note: Finalize execution result
    If execution_result does not contain key "final_status":
        Set execution_result with key "final_status" to "completed"
    
    Set execution_result with key "end_time" to current_timestamp
    Set execution_result with key "execution_trace" to execution_trace
    Set execution_result with key "final_belief_state" to current_belief_state
    
    Return execution_result

Process called "select_next_branch" that takes current_branch as PlanBranch and belief_state as BeliefState returns PlanBranch:
    Let child_branches be current_branch with field child_branches
    
    If length of child_branches is equal to 0:
        Return null
    
    Note: Evaluate branch conditions to select appropriate next branch
    For each child_branch in child_branches:
        Let branch_condition be child_branch with field branch_condition
        Let condition_satisfied be evaluate_branch_condition with branch_condition and belief_state
        
        If condition_satisfied is equal to true:
            Return child_branch
    
    Note: If no condition is satisfied, return null (plan exhausted)
    Return null

Note: Main conditional planning coordination
Process called "create_conditional_planning_system" that takes configuration as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let system be empty dictionary
    Set system with key "planning_algorithms" to configuration with key "algorithms" or list containing "contingent_planning", "conformant_planning"
    Set system with key "uncertainty_models" to configuration with key "uncertainty" or list containing "probabilistic", "possibilistic"
    Set system with key "observation_strategies" to configuration with key "observation" or list containing "information_gain", "cost_benefit"
    Set system with key "plan_execution" to configuration with key "execution" or true
    Set system with key "dynamic_replanning" to configuration with key "replanning" or true
    
    Return system

Process called "execute_conditional_planning_analysis" that takes system as Dictionary and query as Dictionary returns Dictionary:
    Let query_type be query with key "type"
    Let result be empty dictionary
    
    If query_type is equal to "create_conditional_plan":
        Let problem be query with key "problem"
        Let planner_config be query with key "planner_config"
        
        Let planner be create_conditional_planner with planner_config
        Let planning_result be plan_with_conditions with planner and problem
        Set result with key "conditional_planning_result" to planning_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "conformant_plan":
        Let problem be query with key "problem"
        Let planner_config be query with key "planner_config"
        
        Let planner be create_conditional_planner with planner_config
        Set planner with key "planning_algorithm" to "conformant_planning"
        Let planning_result be plan_with_conditions with planner and problem
        Set result with key "conformant_planning_result" to planning_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "execute_conditional_plan":
        Let conditional_plan be query with key "conditional_plan"
        Let execution_config be query with key "execution_config"
        
        Let execution_result be execute_conditional_plan with conditional_plan and execution_config
        Set result with key "execution_result" to execution_result
    
    If query_type is equal to "evaluate_plan_robustness":
        Let conditional_plan be query with key "conditional_plan"
        Let uncertainty_scenarios be query with key "scenarios"
        
        Let robustness_analysis be evaluate_conditional_plan_robustness with conditional_plan and uncertainty_scenarios
        Set result with key "robustness_analysis" to robustness_analysis
    
    If query_type is equal to "optimize_observation_strategy":
        Let problem be query with key "problem"
        Let observation_budget be query with key "budget"
        
        Let optimized_strategy be optimize_observation_placement with problem and observation_budget
        Set result with key "optimized_observation_strategy" to optimized_strategy
    
    Note: Add metadata
    Set result with key "conditional_planning_timestamp" to current_timestamp
    Set result with key "system_config" to extract_system_summary with system
    
    Return result